Frank Wolff (actor) https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frank_Wolff_(actor) 0 Walter Frank Hermann Wolff (May 11, 1928 – December 12, 1971) was an American actor whose film career began with roles in five 1958–61 Roger Corman productions and ended a decade later in Rome, after many appearances in European-made films, most of which were lensed in Italy.
